{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.55",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 55,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 55 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:1",
      "text": "Give ear to my prayer, O God; and hide not thyself from my supplication!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:2",
      "text": "Attend to me, and answer me; I am overcome by my trouble. I am distraught",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:3",
      "text": "by the noise of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked. For they bring trouble upon me, and in anger they cherish enmity against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:4",
      "text": "My heart is in anguish within me, the terrors of death have fallen upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:5",
      "text": "Fear and trembling come upon me, and horror overwhelms me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:6",
      "text": "And I say, “O that I had wings like a dove! I would fly away and be at rest;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:7",
      "text": "yea, I would wander afar, I would lodge in the wilderness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:8",
      "text": "I would haste to find me a shelter from the raging wind and tempest.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:9",
      "text": "Destroy their plans, O Lord, confuse their tongues; for I see violence and strife in the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:10",
      "text": "Day and night they go around it on its walls; and mischief and trouble are within it,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:11",
      "text": "ruin is in its midst; oppression and fraud do not depart from its market place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:12",
      "text": "It is not an enemy who taunts me— then I could bear it; it is not an adversary who deals insolently with me— then I could hide from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:13",
      "text": "But it is you, my equal, my companion, my familiar friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:14",
      "text": "We used to hold sweet converse together; within God's house we walked in fellowship.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:15",
      "text": "Let death come upon them; let them go down to Sheol alive; let them go away in terror into their graves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:16",
      "text": "But I call upon God; and the Lord will save me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:17",
      "text": "Evening and morning and at noon I utter my complaint and moan, and he will hear my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:18",
      "text": "He will deliver my soul in safety from the battle that I wage, for many are arrayed against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:19",
      "text": "God will give ear, and humble them, he who is enthroned from of old; because they keep no law, and do not fear God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:20",
      "text": "My companion stretched out his hand against his friends, he violated his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:21",
      "text": "His speech was smoother than butter, yet war was in his heart; his words were softer than oil, yet they were drawn swords.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:22",
      "text": "Cast your burden on the Lord, and he will sustain you; he will never permit the righteous to be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.55.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 55,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 55:23",
      "text": "But thou, O God, wilt cast them down into the lowest pit; men of blood and treachery shall not live out half their days. But I will trust in thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
